HOW ROUTE53 DOES IT
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

instead of ALB weights
Route53 uses WEIGHTED ROUTING POLICY
at DNS level


SETUP
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

2 DNS records same name different weight

Record 1:
  name    = app.example.com
  type    = A
  value   = ALB-Blue DNS
  weight  = 100
  set-id  = blue

Record 2:
  name    = app.example.com
  type    = A
  value   = ALB-Green DNS
  weight  = 0
  set-id  = green


BLUE/GREEN WITH ROUTE53
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

before:
  app.example.com
    → blue  weight 100  → ALB-Blue  → EC2 old ✅
    → green weight 0    → ALB-Green → EC2 new 🔄

after testing:
  app.example.com
    → blue  weight 0    → ALB-Blue  → EC2 old ❌
    → green weight 100  → ALB-Green → EC2 new ✅

instant switch at DNS level


